{"article_id":"Avmu9e3Jl1tKEbGH","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"John Boehner privately told conservatives","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"that they should feel relieved .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"|","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"John Shinkle/ The GOP 's debt ceiling surrender","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"Less than three years ago , House Speaker John Boehner boldly demanded \" trillions \" in spending cuts in exchange","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"for raising the national borrowing limit .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"\" Let me be as clear","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"as I can be , \"","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"Boehner told the Economic Club of New York in May 2011 .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"\" Without significant spending cuts and reforms","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"to reduce our debt ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"there will be no debt limit increase . \"","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"Boehner violated his own rule","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"by allowing the White House to win a year-long increase of the debt ceiling","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"- with no strings attached .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"Senate Republican leaders urged their members to allow a quick final vote on Wednesday","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"and drop filibuster attempts","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"to prolong the debate .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"In a private lunch , Senate Republicans were more concerned about \" getting the hell out of town \" before an impending snowstorm","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"than digging in on a fight","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"they once relished ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"according to a GOP senator .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"And Boehner even privately told conservatives Tuesday","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"they should be relieved","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"because the concession got the \" monkey off our backs , \"","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"sources said .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"The sharp shift in tactics within the House and Senate GOP caucuses reflects a hardening realization after three years of partisan brinkmanship over the budget :","depth":5},{"id":27,"text":"Fighting over the debt in a crisis-like atmosphere is a political loser .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"\" I ' m one","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"who truly believes","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"if we get this issue behind us ,","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"and behave ourselves ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"we ' ll be in the majority here on this side , in the next six months , \"","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"said Sen. Dean Heller","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"( R-Nev. ) .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"The White House refused to negotiate over a debt ceiling hike .","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"That left Republican leaders with a choice :","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Tie provisions like the Keystone pipeline or Obamacare changes to a debt hike","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"to rally the rank and file","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"or capitulate to Democrats","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"and move past the fight .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"Choosing the first option wasn ' t attractive","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"since several dozen hard-line conservatives in the House would never vote to raise the debt ceiling ,","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"meaning the GOP wouldn ' t be able to push through a bill on its own .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"And with only 45 seats in the Senate , Republicans there weren ' t in a better position","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"to drive policy .","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"Not wanting to relive a debt-crisis similar to the 16-day October government shutdown ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"which","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"polls showed","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"hurt Republicans ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"Boehner had little leverage","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"to exact policy concessions from Democrats .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"And","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"with Republicans betting their 2014 election hopes on the ongoing problems with Obamacare ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"it made little sense to GOP leaders to engage in a divisive intraparty battle","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that they would likely lose .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"\" We could ' ve asked for a copy machine","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"and the president would ' ve been willing to default on the debt","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"just to make a political point , \"","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"said Rep. Raul Labrador","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"( R-Idaho ) ,","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"who voted against the bill .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"\" I think","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"that ' s shameful . \"","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"Since the October deal","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"to reopen the government ,","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"which also effectively raised the debt ceiling through this month ,","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"Republicans have increasingly buckled on budget matters .","depth":4},{"id":69,"text":"They agreed to Democratic demands","depth":5},{"id":70,"text":"to raise discretionary spending caps in a two-year budget deal , something","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"that led to the quick approval of a $ 1.1 trillion spending package last month .","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"\" The shutdown politics was not good for those of us","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"who care about deficit reduction , \"","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"said Sen. Jeff Flake","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"( R-Ariz. ) .","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"Boehner long ago recognized the shifting dynamics of these fiscal fights :","depth":4},{"id":77,"text":"the Senate and White House were holding strong ,","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"and he likely couldn ' t fight that .","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"There was no way","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"he would propose a \" clean \" debt-ceiling increase to House Republicans at the beginning of this fight","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"- even though senior members of leadership knew","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"that ' s where they would end up .","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"Instead , they cycled through a host of options ,","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"demonstrating","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"that none had support .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"Going back-and-forth over a variety of options infuriated several figures in the conference","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"- including some in and around his own leadership table -","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"who hated to see their party struggle to coalesce around a proposal in plain view .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"But Boehner was ultimately successful","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"- perhaps for the first time -","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"at avoiding the messy brinksmanship","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"that typically mark these fights .","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"On Monday evening ,","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"after Republican whips circled the House floor ,","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"it was clear that the last-ditch , Hail Mary option","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"- tying a debt ceiling increase to restoring pension cuts to future military retirees -","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"also had little support .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":195,"left":162,"right":194,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":162,"left":101,"right":161,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":99,"right":100,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":100,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":132,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":122,"right":131,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":111,"right":121,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":111,"left":108,"right":110,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"